01: Angles¶

Sensor details¶

05 March 2019

17:17

<<2_Sensor 26_3um_3D Hetro Nanostructures CoFe_drawing of crosses before measurments 05_03_2019.pdf>>

  • This sensor is old fabicated by Merlin. It has 3µm cross size.

  • It has been handed to Fabritizo to grow these structures shown below

Loading inside the IVC¶

05 March 2019

17:30

  • The sensor Has been loaded on the Yoke directly after taking it out

    from the SEM chamber.

  • Closing the IVC very quick.

  • Pumping out the IVC for two hours (10^-5 mbar)

Loading inside Janis¶

06 March 2019

09:30

  • Mohanad, Jens and Jonathan, managed to load the IVC inside Janis. The

    process was very gentle and the He level was 15 in. We let the system relax and filled He after 1 hour.

Introducing an exchange gas¶

attention please!!¶

06 March 2019

13:30

Important Notes:

  • We had problem when we introduced and exchange gas. The temperature

    was around 200K and we introduced 1mbar for 1s. The process of cooling was very fast and we lost a lot of He(l). The cooling rate was very high and we reached 4k in 1.5 hour. That was not good and we should next time wait at least one day to cool naturally and then intorduce an exchange gas.

    Important Notes:

    Don’t introduce exchange gas too early (T > 200 K)

    Be careful and introduce as little exchange gas as possible
